article.headline: IUPUI 63, Green Bay 46
article.story: OXFORD, Ohio -- Leroy Nobles scored a game-high 21 points and Alex Young added 18 to help IUPUI blow out Wisconsin-Green Bay 63-46 in the O'Reilly Auto Parts CBE Classic on Monday. The Jaguars (2-3) jumped out to a 19-4 lead with 10:17 left in the first half after Nobles converted a layup with Young assisting. IUPUI maintained the advantage until halftime, 29-15, thanks to 10-for-19 shooting (52.6 percent) in the opening half. The Phoenix (2-3) struggled to make anything in the opening half as they shot just 6 for 30 from the floor (20 percent). Green Bay's shooting improved in the second -- 12 of 25 for 48 percent -- but it still wasn't enough. Rahmon Fletcher was the only player in double figures for the Phoenix with 16 points on 8-of-10 shooting (80 percent) from the floor. Stephen Thomas added 16 points -- 13 in the first half -- for the Jaguars on 3-of-5 shooting (60 percent) from 3-point range.
